FBIS4-17589 "drsov080_l_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-080 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 Kyrgyzstan Akayev Undergoes Surgery in Moscow Akayev Undergoes Surgery in Moscow LD2504105694 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0400 GMT 25 Apr 94 LD2504105694 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network Kazakh BFN [Text] Of late President Askar Akayev of Kyrgyzstan has had a surgical operation, reports the international ASIA newspaper. The population, who very often see him attending meetings or speaking on television, is unlikely to think the president is prone to fall ill. The president, who looks quite fit, was operated on at one of the hospitals in Moscow and resumed his duties immediately after his return to the Republic.
